So the mechanism is: `stash_diagnostic_error` stores an error in thread-local storage, and `take_diagnostic_error` retrieves and clears it. This is meant for startup errors that happen before the state event file is available — so when `yyds state why last-failure` is run on a cold start, it can say "hey, actually, there was this error during startup that might explain why nothing's recorded."

